{"_id":"@byted-service/consul","author":{"email":"yeyuanfeng@bytedance.com","name":"Yaphet Ye"},"dist-tags":{"alpha":"2.1.3-alpha.0","beta":"3.0.0-beta.1","latest":"2.1.6"},"readme":"# @byted-service/consul 服务发现\n\n[![bnpm](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/badge/v/@byted-service/consul.svg?style=flat-square)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/consul) [![download](https://2y8ngapf.fn.bytedance.net/d?p=@byted-service/consul)](https://web-bnpm.byted.org/package/@byted-service/consul)\n\n[简体中文](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/consul/README.md) | [English](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/consul/README.en.md) | [CHANGELOG](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/blob/master/packages/consul/CHANGELOG.md)\n\n> The following is **@byted-service/consul@2.x** document, **1.x** document see [consul-v1.x](https://code.byted.org/nodejs/byted-service/tree/consul-v1.x/packages/consul), [@byted-service/consul@2.0.0 release log](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnwU1HWzEOsAiWDdkrMCdNqh).\n\n**@byted-service/consul** is the basic service discovery `SDK` on the `Node.js` side of the company. It is widely integrated in `@byted-service/xxx`. See [Node.js Service Discovery ( Consul ) User Guide](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnU8nNhyPfhV2OjHLCVQPX5g), [A Quick Start with Service Discovery ( Consul ) for Front-End Engineers](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcn9QfY7pMwo9I9Jf1Y2q6R4d).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install @byted-service/consul --registry=http://bnpm.byted.org\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```ts\n// consul.ts\nimport { lookup, lookupName, random, Consul } from '@byted-service/consul';\n\n(async () => {\n    console.log(await lookup('p.s.m'));\n    console.log(await lookupName('p.s.m'));\n    console.log(await random('p.s.m'));\n\n    const consul = new Consul();\n\n    console.log(await consul.lookup('p.s.m'));\n})();\n```\n\n```ts\nROUTE_IP=10.225.130.44 ts-node consul.ts\n```\n\nPS: `10.225.130.44` is the `IP` of the public development machine.\n\n## API\n\n### lookup(psm[, options[, consul]])\n\nGet the service registration address of `PSM`.\n\n-   `psm`: Service `PSM`.\n-   `options`\n    -   `cluster`: Service `Cluster`.\n    -   `idc`: Service `IDC`.\n    -   `addrfam`: Service `address family` filter.\n        -   `dual-stack`: Return `IPv4 + IPv6` address.\n        -   `v4`: Return `IPv4` address.\n        -   `v6`: Return `IPv6` address.\n    -   `unique`: Service address merging conditions will only take effect when `options.addrfam` is `dual-stack`.\n        -   `v4`: Based on `IPv4`.\n        -   `v6`: Based on `IPv6`.\n    -   `limit`: Return number.\n    -   `nocache`: Whether not to use cache.\n    -   `consulHash`: The value of `x-consul-result-hash` used when requesting `Consul Agent`.\n    -   `timeout`: Request timeout, the unit is `ms`, the default value is `3s`.\n-   `consul`: `Consul` instance, the default value is `new Consul()`.\n\n### lookupName(psm[, options[, consul]])\n\nGet the service registration address of `PSM`, which is different from `lookup()`. It will automatically add `options.addrfam` and `options.unique` parameters according to the `BYTED_HOST_IP` and `BYTED_HOST_IPV6` environment variables. See:\n\n-   [Node.js dual-stack ( ipv4 + ipv6 ) upgrade](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnwT1YeXEEGN3zZVlzxxazEd).\n-   [Infrastructure IPv6 Upgrade Manual ( For Business )](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcn7ufZcNgRKH8w53IPSME4vg).\n-   [Enable ipv6 support](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnVVJN7FXM6XZ6POqYMsFn1c).\n\n<!--  -->\n\n-   `psm`: Service `PSM`.\n-   `options`\n    -   `cluster`: Service `Cluster`.\n    -   `idc`: Service `IDC`.\n    -   `addrfam`: Service `address family` filter.\n        -   `dual-stack`: Return `IPv4 + IPv6` address.\n        -   `v4`: Return `IPv4` address.\n        -   `v6`: Return `IPv6` address.\n    -   `unique`: Service address merging conditions will only take effect when `options.addrfam` is `dual-stack`.\n        -   `v4`: Based on `IPv4`.\n        -   `v6`: Based on `IPv6`.\n    -   `limit`: Return number.\n    -   `nocache`: Whether not to use cache.\n    -   `consulHash`: The value of `x-consul-result-hash` used when requesting `Consul Agent`.\n    -   `timeout`: Request timeout, the unit is `ms`, the default value is `3s`.\n-   `consul`: `Consul` instance, the default value is `new Consul()`.\n\n### random(psm[, options[, consul]])\n\nRandomly get a service registration address of `PSM` ( weighted random ).\n\n-   `psm`: Service `PSM`.\n-   `options`\n    -   `cluster`: Service `Cluster`.\n    -   `idc`: Service `IDC`.\n    -   `addrfam`: Service `address family` filter.\n        -   `dual-stack`: Return `IPv4 + IPv6` address.\n        -   `v4`: Return `IPv4` address.\n        -   `v6`: Return `IPv6` address.\n    -   `unique`: Service address merging conditions will only take effect when `options.addrfam` is `dual-stack`.\n        -   `v4`: Based on `IPv4`.\n        -   `v6`: Based on `IPv6`.\n    -   `limit`: Return number.\n    -   `nocache`: Whether not to use cache.\n    -   `consulHash`: The value of `x-consul-result-hash` used when requesting `Consul Agent`.\n    -   `timeout`: Request timeout, the unit is `ms`, the default value is `3s`.\n-   `consul`: `Consul` instance, the default value is `new Consul()`.\n\n### new Consul(\\[options\\])\n\n-   `options`\n    -   `host`: `Consul Agent Host`.\n    -   `port`: `Consul Agent Port`.\n    -   `socketPath`: `Consul Agent UDS ( Unix Domain Socket )`.\n    -   `logger`: `Logger` instance.\n    -   `enableWarning`: Whether to output `warning`, the local default is `false`.\n    -   `cacheTime`: Cache time, the unit is `ms`, the default value is `15s`.\n    -   `debug`: Whether to enable `debug` ( for debugging ), the default value is `false`.\n\n### consul.address\n\n`Consul Agent Address`.\n\n### consul.lookup(psm[, options])\n\nGet the service registration address of `PSM`.\n\n-   `psm`: Service `PSM`.\n-   `options`\n    -   `cluster`: Service `Cluster`.\n    -   `idc`: Service `IDC`.\n    -   `addrfam`: Service `address family` filter.\n        -   `dual-stack`: Return `IPv4 + IPv6` address.\n        -   `v4`: Return `IPv4` address.\n        -   `v6`: Return `IPv6` address.\n    -   `unique`: Service address merging conditions will only take effect when `options.addrfam` is `dual-stack`.\n        -   `v4`: Based on `IPv4`.\n        -   `v6`: Based on `IPv6`.\n    -   `limit`: Return number.\n    -   `nocache`: Whether not to use cache.\n    -   `consulHash`: The value of `x-consul-result-hash` used when requesting `Consul Agent`.\n    -   `timeout`: Request timeout, the unit is `ms`, the default value is `3s`.\n-   `consul`: `Consul` instance, the default value is `new Consul()`.\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n### Consul Agent Uds Path\n\nEnvironment variables:\n\n-   `BYTED_SD_UDS_PATH`\n\n```shell\n# At this time, the service registration address of PSM will be got from /path/to/consul.sock.\nBYTED_SD_UDS_PATH=/path/to/consul.sock node app.js\n```\n\nPriority:\n\n-   `BYTED_SD_UDS_PATH` > Consul Agent Host\n\n### Consul Agent Host\n\nEnvironment variables:\n\n-   `CONSUL_HTTP_HOST`\n-   `MY_HOST_IP`\n-   `TCE_HOST_IP`\n-   `MY_HOST_IPV6`\n-   `ROUTE_IP`\n\n```shell\n# At this time, the service registration address of PSM will be got from 10.225.130.44:2280.\nCONSUL_HTTP_HOST=10.225.130.44 node app.js\n```\n\nPriority:\n\n-   `CONSUL_HTTP_HOST` > `MY_HOST_IP` > `TCE_HOST_IP` > `MY_HOST_IPV6` > `ROUTE_IP`\n\n### Consul Agent Port\n\nEnvironment variables:\n\n-   `CONSUL_HTTP_PORT`\n\n```shell\n# At this time, the service registration address of PSM will be got from 127.0.0.1:3000.\nCONSUL_HTTP_HOST=127.0.0.1 CONSUL_HTTP_PORT=3000 node app.js\n```\n\n## FAQ\n\n### ETIMEOUT & ECONNREFUSED\n\nWhen developing locally, the following errors may be encountered:\n\n```sh\nError: connect ETIMEOUT 10.17.91.134:2280\n```\n\nThis is because `@byted-service/consul` will use the address `10.17.91.134:2280` for service discovery. If the address has expired or the network is isolated, the above error may occur. At this time, you can avoid this problem by setting the `CONSUL_HTTP_HOST` environment variable.\n\n```sh\n# At this time, the service registration address of PSM will be got from 10.225.130.44:2280.\nCONSUL_HTTP_HOST=10.225.130.44 node app.js\n```\n\nPS: `10.225.130.44` is the `IP` of the public development machine.\n\n### Local To Boe\n\nThere is generally no network isolation between local and `boe` ( except `boe-i18n` ), so service discovery can be performed directly.\n\n1. Get the `Devbox` or `Boe` machine `IP` ( assuming it is `10.225.130.44` ).\n2. Set the `CONSUL_HTTP_HOST` environment variable.\n\n```sh\n# At this time, the service registration address of PSM will be got from 10.225.130.44:2280.\nCONSUL_HTTP_HOST=10.225.130.44 node app.js\n```\n\nPS: `TCE` machine `IP` maybe change, therefore, please use `Devbox` machine `IP` in most cases.\n\n### Local To PPE / Prod\n\nThere is network isolation between the local and `PPE` / `Prod`, so service discovery cannot be performed directly, and you need to apply for escape first, see [Office-Production Network Access Restriction](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnkCENdx6SWyeKo3belNpj6f).\n\n1. Get the `PPE` or `Prod` machine `IP` ( assuming it is `10.0.0.1` ).\n2. Set the `CONSUL_HTTP_HOST` environment variable.\n\n```sh\n# At this time, the service registration address of PSM will be got from 10.0.0.1:2280.\nCONSUL_HTTP_HOST=10.0.0.1 node app.js\n```\n\n### Boe To PPE / Prod\n\nThere is network isolation between the `Boe` and `PPE` / `Prod`, so service discovery cannot be performed directly, and you need to apply for escape first, see [BOE - Production Access Isolation](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnJlbtFF8bonFtJusyBysFUt).\n\n1. Get the `PPE` or `Prod` machine `IP` ( assuming it is `10.0.0.1` ).\n2. Set the `CONSUL_HTTP_HOST` environment variable.\n\n```sh\n# At this time, the service registration address of PSM will be got from 10.0.0.1:2280.\nCONSUL_HTTP_HOST=10.0.0.1 node app.js\n```\n\n### Devbox to Boe\n\nThere is generally no network isolation between `Devbox` and `boe` ( except `boe-i18n` ), so service discovery can be performed directly.\n\n1. Get the `Devbox` or `Boe` machine `IP` ( assuming it is `10.225.130.44` ).\n2. Set the `CONSUL_HTTP_HOST` environment variable.\n\n```sh\n# At this time, the service registration address of PSM will be got from 10.225.130.44:2280.\nCONSUL_HTTP_HOST=10.225.130.44 node app.js\n```\n\n### Devbox to PPE / Prod\n\nThere is network isolation between the `Devbox` and `PPE` / `Prod`, so service discovery cannot be performed directly, and you need to apply for escape first, see [Devbox - Production Access Isolation](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnI1e3EbOm9dyPiupGtUM2Lb).\n\n1. Get the `PPE` or `Prod` machine `IP` ( assuming it is `10.0.0.1` ).\n2. Set the `CONSUL_HTTP_HOST` environment variable.\n\n```sh\n# At this time, the service registration address of PSM will be got from 10.0.0.1:2280.\nCONSUL_HTTP_HOST=10.0.0.1 node app.js\n```\n\n## Documents\n\n-   [@Byted-service/ consul @ 2.0.0 Release log](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnwU1HWzEOsAiWDdkrMCdNqh).\n-   [Node.js Service Discovery ( Consul ) User Guide](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnU8nNhyPfhV2OjHLCVQPX5g).\n-   [A Quick Start with Service Discovery ( Consul ) for Front-End Engineers](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcn9QfY7pMwo9I9Jf1Y2q6R4d).\n-   [Node.js dual-stack ( ipv4 + ipv6 ) upgrade](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnwT1YeXEEGN3zZVlzxxazEd).\n-   [Infrastructure IPv6 Upgrade Manual ( For Business )](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcn7ufZcNgRKH8w53IPSME4vg).\n-   [Enable ipv6 support](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/wiki/wikcnVVJN7FXM6XZ6POqYMsFn1c).\n-   [Devbox / BOE and production network domain name exchange visit instructions](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnmTz3UPQOpucYFedFASnT8e).\n-   [Office-Production Network Access Restriction](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnkCENdx6SWyeKo3belNpj6f).\n-   [BOE - Production Access Isolation](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnJlbtFF8bonFtJusyBysFUt).\n-   [Devbox - Production Access Isolation](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnI1e3EbOm9dyPiupGtUM2Lb).\n-   [BOE Mac and Devbox test method summary](https://bytedance.feishu.cn/docs/doccnllkQa3fhBbkss3EPMm935c).\n","time":{"1.0.5":"2018-09-06T03:31:18.301Z","1.12.2":"2020-12-22T06:44:30.667Z","1.11.9":"2020-10-28T05:06:55.246Z","2.1.6":"2024-07-26T03:57:26.707Z","1.0.0":"2018-08-17T02:29:06.159Z","1.11.2":"2020-07-02T04:04:42.257Z","1.5.3":"2019-10-24T01:58:13.341Z","1.6.0-beta.1":"2019-11-22T14:00:17.501Z","1.0.2":"2018-08-22T07:45:16.898Z","1.0.6":"2018-09-17T02:30:15.212Z","1.6.1":"2019-12-06T10:30:38.673Z","1.7.0":"2020-04-07T02:48:05.476Z","3.0.0-beta.1":"2023-04-10T09:14:45.154Z","1.0.4":"2018-09-04T05:01:07.820Z","1.11.6":"2020-08-31T11:36:05.252Z","1.12.5":"2021-05-08T08:24:59.420Z","2.1.3-beta.0":"2022-06-23T10:08:07.964Z","1.10.0":"2020-06-16T02:02:34.690Z","1.11.10":"2020-11-27T02:51:18.359Z","1.7.1":"2020-05-18T06:27:28.287Z","1.1.1":"2018-12-11T02:11:47.280Z","1.3.0":"2019-05-27T03:35:57.538Z","3.0.0-beta.0":"2023-03-31T03:35:10.927Z","1.1.4":"2019-05-13T09:29:15.352Z","1.8.0":"2020-05-25T03:05:36.950Z","1.6.3":"2020-03-01T12:45:28.218Z","2.0.0":"2021-12-01T05:31:54.571Z","2.1.4":"2022-07-21T02:08:15.021Z","1.12.8":"2021-07-05T09:30:57.531Z","1.5.0":"2019-09-03T09:43:49.771Z","1.6.0":"2019-12-05T10:45:51.040Z","2.1.3-alpha.0":"2022-06-23T09:58:37.023Z","1.12.6":"2021-05-19T07:34:07.983Z","1.4.2":"2019-09-03T09:43:40.488Z","1.3.2":"2019-07-23T08:52:49.821Z","1.4.1":"2019-08-16T05:30:54.248Z","1.9.0":"2020-05-27T10:31:51.569Z","2.1.2":"2022-03-30T03:45:11.909Z","1.11.7":"2020-10-09T02:56:13.044Z","1.12.9":"2021-11-19T02:43:32.297Z","1.1.2":"2018-12-27T09:05:45.927Z","1.12.4":"2021-04-29T06:33:28.089Z",